The Los Angeles County Sheriff’s Department was in a heated standoff Friday afternoon with a man who allegedly entered one of its stations and tried to set it on fire. The unnamed suspect entered the LASD Century Division station in South Los Angeles with a gas can before his failed arson attempt, CBS News Los Angeles reported. The man then fled, got into a white Lincoln Navigator and tried to escape. Authorities chased him down and surrounded his car, asking for him to surrender at around 12:30 p.m. The standoff ensued until 1:45 p.m. when the suspect exited his vehicle and was taken into custody, CBS LA reported. There is no explanation for the man’s motive.